DATABASE SUMMARY

This screen lists the databases that Replicator recognizes.  By default,
the local database information that you entered in the Define Local
Database form appears in the list.  You must add all other databases
that belong to your replication scheme to the list.

The columns of the list are:

        COLUMN NAME     DESCRIPTION
        -----------     -----------
        No.             The database number.  This is a unique
                        system-wide identifier assigned by the user.

        Database        The virtual node name plus the database name.

        Owner           The owner (DBA) of the database.

        DBMS Type       The type of database, for example, Ingres
                        or CA-Datacom.

        Remarks         A short comment.


The menu commands are as follows:

        MENU COMMAND    SYNOPSIS
        ------------    --------
        Add             Add a new database to the list.

        Delete          Delete the currently highlighted database.  You
                        will be asked for confirmation.

        Edit            Edit the information for the currently
                        highlighted database.

        Help            Access the Help facility.

        End             Return to the Configuration Menu.
